---
import Section from "./Section.astro";
import Card from "./Card.astro";
---

<Section id="pillars" className="pillars">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header" data-reveal>
      <p class="eyebrow">Engineering pillars</p>
      <h2>Built to scale, perform, and stay maintainable.</h2>
      <p class="section-body">
        Four pillars that keep releases stable even when requirements change, with security built
        into the engineering work.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="pillars-grid">
      <Card className="pillar-card" data-reveal style="--delay: 40ms">
        <h3>System integrity</h3>
        <p>Clean architecture, tested changes, and secure coding standards built in.</p>
        <ul class="bullet-list">
          <li>White-box testing and code reviews</li>
          <li>Secure coding checks in every release</li>
        </ul>
      </Card>
      <Card className="pillar-card" data-reveal style="--delay: 80ms">
        <h3>Scalable architecture</h3>
        <p>Modular services, reliable data models, and infrastructure that grows with you.</p>
        <ul class="bullet-list">
          <li>Capacity forecasting</li>
          <li>Access boundaries for core services</li>
        </ul>
      </Card>
      <Card className="pillar-card" data-reveal style="--delay: 120ms">
        <h3>Reliability focus</h3>
        <p>Observability, incident readiness, and performance budgets baked in.</p>
        <ul class="bullet-list">
          <li>On-call playbooks</li>
          <li>Incident response and vulnerability triage</li>
        </ul>
      </Card>
      <Card className="pillar-card" data-reveal style="--delay: 160ms">
        <h3>Clean delivery</h3>
        <p>Readable code, strong documentation, and automated testing from day one.</p>
        <ul class="bullet-list">
          <li>Weekly demos</li>
          <li>Release docs with dependency checks</li>
        </ul>
      </Card>
    </div>
  </div>
</Section>
